Today started out overcast then turned sunny.  Then today went from sunny and pleasant to sunny with a stiff and chilly west wind.

The park rangers stopped in for a visit this afternoon.  The plan I submitted for the wood storage shed was approved.  Now I can add building that shed to my list of chores.  One chore that did get marked off today was the one to clear the trail that runs along side the cabin.  Louis helped me with it.  Whenever we take walks in that direction he frequently stops and looks back to see if I am still going in his direction.  When we get to an intersection he will wait for me to signal with my arm which way we will be going.  When he sees the signal he will then head off in that direction.

<a href="http://www.notesfromalaska.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/louisontrail.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-884" src="http://www.notesfromalaska.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/louisontrail.jpg" alt="louisontrail" width="640" height="360" /></a>

I went fishing this evening.  One of the rangers was down there fishing too.  She was using a very heavy rod and reel designed for surf fishing.  I asked if she wanted to try my outfit just to see the difference.  On her first cast she caught a King Salmon.  Four casts later she caught another one.

I finally got my rod back and proceeded to beat the water to a froth casting and reeling, casting and reeling.  I didn't get a single strike!  Go figure that one out!

In the last 24 hours about ten new people have signed up to read these postings.  Did any of you regular readers have anything to do with this appreciated activity?  I am wondering if by chance some spam thing has added these new users.  Any information about where all these new readers came from would be helpful.  Thanks,

&nbsp;

