I went exploring today. There is a place back away from the coast called Bear Island. It is about two miles back a seldom used trail. I must have driven by this trail 20 times and never noticed it. People had told me where it was so today I paid more attention and drove slower and found it.   There is an old cabin at the base of the rock. Some years ago it must have been a nice place.

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

<a href="http://www.notesfromalaska.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/bearisland.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-887" src="http://www.notesfromalaska.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/bearisland.jpg" alt="bearisland" width="640" height="360" /></a> Bear Island is the highest place around here. It is dominated by a huge rock left there thousands of years ago if not longer. I think everybody here knew how to get there except me. Bear Island is where we are supposed to go if there is a tsunami. That trail is the evacuation route! We better have plenty of warning if there is a need to evacuate. To get up on that rock takes a lot of bushwhacking.<a href="http://www.notesfromalaska.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/topview.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-890" src="http://www.notesfromalaska.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/topview.jpg" alt="topview" width="640" height="360" /></a>

