It was a nice day here.  The sky was mostly clear until around six this evening when it began misting.  The misting started just as Adam and I were putting the boat back in the water.  He was interested in how one goes about commercial fishing here.  Adam helped me with the rope the other day and he wanted a few fish to smoke.  I thought we would put a net in the water for an hour or so, catch maybe six or eight fish then quit.  Earlier the Vet had told me he limited out fly fishing for Silvers this morning.  This afternoon around he was back out there casting to the fish with no hook in the fly he was using.  There were fish everywhere.  He was just having fun having them strike his fly and then pull it harmlessly back and cast again.

Anyway ,Adam and I set a short net on upstream from the Vet figuring we would catch a few of those confused fish who had just had their treat taken away from them.  We caught one spawned out Silver and didn't keep it it was so deteriorated.

